      "lineNbr": 71,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-29T02:02:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In datastore this basically requires a transaction that touches O(N) entity groups (or doing fanout through a separate transactional task queue task). It may be possible Spanner has similar performance challenges here (i.e. these transactions will be slow or flaky).\n\nBut do I understand correctly that we won\u0027t have invocations with many parents?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 71,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "57de094054dbccd6bdb8c1415b00f6e02a6f4c3b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "98124a63_d4a3fd9e",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/backend/invocation_finalization.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 71,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-29T23:03:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "in spanner, locking is done at *cell level*, which is pretty nice here. We lock ONLY on invocation state. \n\nyeah, not a lot of parents. A swarming task deduplication works only for completed tasks. Only CQAttempt:Build invocation applies here and we don\u0027t expect a lot of cq attempts that reuse the same build. The worst case here is a lot CLs in a CrOS CL set with a bunch of trivial rebases and CQDryRuns on each CL. We\u0027d read inv state of all of them.",
      "parentUuid": "f9f3137a_f2c32140",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 71,
        "endChar": 20
      },
